TopicTitle: Crashing when going back to space center

Articles.Content: That looks like KSP is hitting the 32-bit process memory limit. See the [thread=92229]How to Get Support[/thread] sticky for general advice and what information to provide if that's not the problem.

Adding OpenGL or DX11 switch to the shortcut and installing active texture management and temp gauge killer should help.

http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/84203-Less-memory-usage-by-using-OpenGL

http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/106356-Forcing-DirectX11-40-memory-reduction%21

http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/59005-1-0-Release-5-0-April-28-2015-Active-Texture-Management-Save-RAM!

http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/120731

Hopefully the scene change and temp gauge memory leaks gets fixed soonish. Or we get 64bit support

Hello,

I have the exact same issue. No mods installed except MechJeb (never used a part from it). I placed a rover inside a 2.5m cargo bay. Afyer the start the cargo bay starts to vibrate and when I choose to go back to "Assembly" the game crashes. It is only from this particullar vehicle... First i thought that it is because some parts from the rover are sticking out from the closed cargo bay as when i open the doors the vibrations will stop. After that I fixed all parts so everything is inside the bay but it is the same. My only option is to move/delete decoupler which is hodling the rover inside the bay. I hsve offsetted it so maybe it is somehow interacting with the rest... but still... Why is it not vibrating when the door are open?

Other issue i have with my cargo bay on Mun and Minmus is that in about 7/10 times after the "switch to/load" it will destroy the craft. So i 5hink there is something wrong with the cargo bay...
